title: Grateful Dead Live at Indianapolis Sports and Music Center on 1984-06-30
description:
Set 1

Jack Straw, Dire Wolf, Minglewood Blues, Dupree's Diamond Blues, Far From Me, My Brother Esau-> Ramble On Rose-> Lost Sailor-> Saint Of Circumstance-> Deal

Set 2

Shakedown Street-> Playin' In The Band-> Terrapin Station-> Drums-> Playin' In The Band-> Truckin'-> Spoonful-> Stella Blue-> Goin' Down The Road Feelin' Bad-> One More Saturday Night, E: Day Job

reviews.review_text: Great recording  Thought the show was a tad disappointing though, esp the 2nd set. It's not bad but it's just not as tight and choogling as other shows from June/July. Transition into Playin a bit weird (nice try), Terrapin too saggy, a complete botch of the "rusty strings" line in Stella. Jerry is very hoarse too. Not a bad listen just not up to the quality you'd hope from the 1st half of 2nd set
Best Aud source The Miller mk41pull sounds fairly good. It's a bit bright and seems a bit too fast.  This Nak 700 pull is better balanced and the speed is right.
